2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/microsoft">微软</a>对<a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/activision">动视暴雪</a>的收购已获得英国竞争与市场管理局（CMA）的批准——克服了收购的最后一个障碍。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/gaming-features/stalker-2-heart-of-chornobyl-preview-hands-on-3488629">《潜行者 2：切尔诺贝利之心》预览：残酷，但前景令人难以置信</a></strong></li></ul><p>在微软和动视暴雪宣布将<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/call-of-duty-could-come-to-ubisoft-in-new-activision-microsoft-agreement-3486426">后者游戏的流媒体版权出售给育碧15年</a>之后，CMA暂时批准了此次收购。</p><p>然而，它表示<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/microsoft-gets-one-step-closer-to-buying-call-of-duty-developer-activision-blizzard-3502676">仍然存在“剩余问题”</a> ，需要通过进一步调查来解决。现在新的分析已经结束，预计收购将很快完成。 </p><figure id="attachment_3514574" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3514574" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3514574" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-2.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3514574" class="wp-caption-text">一个人在玩白色 Xbox 控制器 图片来源：Eugene Chystiakov，来自 Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p> “今年 8 月，微软做出让步，<a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/ubisoft">育碧</a>将取代微软购买动视的云游戏版权，”CMA 在<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/microsoft-concession-a-gamechanger-that-will-promote-competition#:~:text=This%20new%20deal%20will%20put,ways%20of%20accessing%20that%20content." target="_blank" rel="noopener">向媒体提供的一份声明</a>中解释道。</p><p> “This new deal will put the cloud streaming rights (outside the European Economic Area) for all of Activision&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/tags/pc">PC</a> and console content produced over the next 15 years in the hands of a strong and independent competitor with ambitious plans to offer new ways of accessing that content.</p><p> “As a result of this concession, the Competition And Markets Authority agreed to look afresh at the deal and launched a new investigation in August. That investigation has completed today with the Competition And Markets Authority clearing this narrower transaction.</p><p> “The new deal will stop Microsoft from locking up competition in cloud gaming as this market takes off, preserving competitive prices and services for United Kingdom cloud gaming customers.” </p><figure id="attachment_3514580" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3514580" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3514580" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-3.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-3.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-3-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-3-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-3-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-3-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/microsoft-activision-acquisition-approved-formally-by-CMA-3-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3514580" class="wp-caption-text"> An Xbox Series X console Credit: Billy Freeman via Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p> “It will allow Ubisoft to offer Activision&#39;s content under any business model, including through multigame subscription services,” it added. “It will also help to ensure that cloud gaming providers will be able to use non-Windows operating systems for Activision content, reducing costs and increasing efficiency.”</p><p> Brad Smith, Microsoft&#39;s vice chair and president, shared his gratitude that the CMA approved of the acquisition at long last. “We have now crossed the final regulatory hurdle to close this acquisition, which we believe will benefit players and the gaming industry worldwide,” he said <a href="https://twitter.com/BradSmi/status/1712711053552107606" target="_blank" rel="noopener">in a post to X</a> .</p><p> Once the acquisition is finalised, Microsoft will own Activision Publishing, <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/blizzard-entertainment">Blizzard Entertainment</a> , King, Major League Gaming, and Activision Blizzard Studios. Within these are the rights to <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/en_asia/games/call-of-duty">Call Of Duty</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/en_asia/games/diablo">Diablo</a> , Candy Crush, <a href="https://www.nme.com/en_asia/games/world-of-warcraft">World Of Warcraft</a></em> and more.</p><p> Appreciably, this will add a lot of influential titles and series under Microsoft&#39;s umbrella, having secured studios like <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/arkane">Arkane</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/bethesda">Bethesda</a> <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/bethesda-softworks">Softworks</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/id-software">id Software</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/machinegames">MachineGames</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/tango-gameworks">Tango Gameworks</a> in 2021.</p><p> In other gaming news, publisher 505 Games <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/exclusive-ghostrunner-2-reveals-first-track-from-returning-composer-daniel-deluxe-3513947">shared one of the tracks</a> from the anticipated cyberpunk action game <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/ghostrunner-2"><em>Ghostrunner 2</em></a> , produced by returning composer Daniel Deluxe.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/microsofts-acquisition-of-activision-blizzard-has-been-approved-by-all-regulators-3514539">Microsoft&#39;s acquisition of Activision Blizzard has been approved by all regulators</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
